article.headline: Wyoming 79, San Diego State 71
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. (AP) -- Wyoming was behind by 13 and looking lethargic when little-used guard Jerry Webb was called off the bench. Webb, a walk-on from Sheridan College, wanted to provide some kind of spark against San Diego State -- offensively, defensively, whatever. He did both. Webb scored 10 points in five minutes at the end of the first half to put Wyoming back in control en route to a 79-71 win over the Aztecs on Monday night. Webb also grabbed five rebounds and was 2-3 from the 3-point arc. "I wasn't really thinking about minutes," Webb said. "They could keep me in there for two minutes. I just wanted to win." Jay Straight scored a career-high 30 points and Alex Dunn added 12 points and 10 rebounds as Wyoming snapped a three-game losing streak overall and a four-game streak against San Diego State with the win. Straight's performance was redemption, of sorts, for his 5-16 shooting -- including 0-7 from the arc -- in Wyoming's loss against UNLV on Saturday. "That's what's good about this conference," he said. "You can't look back on a game. If you struggle you've got to keep your head up and practice hard. Two days later I can come out and have game like I had tonight." Wyoming (9-9, 2-3 Mountain West Conference) fell behind early but grabbed its first lead of the game off a 3-pointer by Dion Sherrell with 2:17 left in the half. Straight scored 21 of his points in the second half as Wyoming caught fire from the 3-point arc and took control of the game. David Adams added 11 points for Wyoming, which hit 62 percent of its free throws and 3-pointers in the second half. Wyoming coach Steve McClain praised his team for pushing the ball up the court, making easy shots and playing hard. "(San Diego State) tried to jump over us and throw a hard pass but then it goes out of bounds," he said. "That was other good thing we did. ... When we needed to get some stops we got a couple stops in there." Wyoming was behind 37-34 early in the second when Straight led the Cowboys on a 17-3 run to give them a 51-40 lead with 13:43 left. San Diego State's Chris Manker kept the Aztecs in the game, hitting four 3-pointers in the second half and scoring 14 points. Brandon Heath added 15 points and Aerick Sanders 12 points and 11 rebounds. The Aztecs came within three points with 2:30 remaining, but Straight put the game away with a 3-point jumper. The Cowboys also hit 9-10 free throws in the last 1:04 to keep them ahead. San Diego State (11-8, 2-2) had won four straight against the Cowboys. The team plays conference leader Air Force on Saturday. Wyoming heads to border rival Colorado State that night -- a game Straight and others were looking forward to. "We're not going to solve all our problems with one win but the kids did a good job," McClain said. "Early it was frustrating but we kept playing hard. That's all I ask of the kids."
